Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Grate the @carrot{1} (no need to peel).

Tear the @smoked salmon{100%grams} into small pieces. IMPORTANT: Wash hands after handling fish.

Slice the @brioche rolls{2} down through the middle (but not all the way through). @?butter{to taste} the bread if you like.

Pop them onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: You can toast your bread in the toaster if you'd like.

Mix the salmon, grated carrot and @aioli{1%sachet} in a #bowl{}.

Mix well and season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Top the bases of the brioche rolls and scatter over the @crispy onions{1%sachet}. Close the sandwich.

To serve, slice each roll in half widthways.

Divide between plates.